    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal from the front passenger side, you say? That's a bit of a giveaway, but I'm no expert, just a regular Joe who's been around the block a few times, like a seasoned goblin who's seen his fair share of dark alleys and narrow escapes. \n\nThat squeal could be related to worn-out brake pads or rotors, which are like the goblins' favorite hiding spots - they can be hiding in plain sight, just waiting to pounce on unsuspecting brake pads. Or, it could be a loose or worn-out brake hose, which is like a goblin's favorite rope - it can get tangled up and cause all sorts of trouble.\n\nI'd recommend checking the brake pads and rotors on the front passenger side, and also inspecting the brake hose for any signs of damage or wear. It's also a good idea to have a professional mechanic take a look, like a goblin who's been around the block a few times and knows the ins and outs of brake systems. They can help you diagnose the issue and recommend the best course of action.",
